# Requirements Management Workflow

## Requirement

SHALL use doorstop commands for requirements management workflow.

## Commands

- `make reqs-init`: Initialize doorstop structure (one-time)
- `make reqs-add`: Add new requirement (interactive)
- `make reqs-edit`: Edit requirements
- `make reqs-validate`: Validate requirement links
- `make reqs-export`: Export to HTML/Markdown/CSV/YAML
- `make reqs-publish`: Generate and publish requirement docs
- `make reqs-tree`: View document tree structure
- `make reqs-help`: Show requirements management help

## Adding Requirements

When adding requirements, SHALL follow this process:

1. **System Requirements**: SHALL use `make reqs-add` and select SYS
2. **Software Requirements**: SHALL use `make reqs-add` and select SRS
3. **Test Cases**: SHALL use `make reqs-add` and select TEST

## Linking Requirements

- SHALL use parent-child relationships in doorstop
- SHALL reference requirements by ID in code comments
- SHALL link test cases to specific software requirements

## StrictDoc Compatibility

- SHALL use doorstop as the primary requirements management tool
- SHALL export doorstop documents to formats compatible with StrictDoc when needed
- SHALL maintain parallel documentation where necessary
- SHALL follow StrictDoc grammar rules when generating StrictDoc files from doorstop exports
